This paper deals with natural language processing and machine translation, which are core topics in the field of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The use of neural networks and deep learning techniques also suggests that this paper could be categorized under cs.AI. Additionally, the paper involves the evaluation of machine-generated text, which falls under the category of natural language generation (cs.NLG). The paper also deals with information retrieval and language modeling, which could place it under cs.IR. Finally, the user study aspect of the paper could suggest a connection to human-computer interaction (cs.HC) or machine learning (cs.LG).
